In this task, the participants pressed as quickly as possible the "j” key if the word "right” appeared on the right side and the "f” key if the word "left” appeared on the left side of a centralized cross on the computer screen. The words "right” or "left” were presented for 900 ms, followed by 600 ms during which only the centralized cross was displayed (see 
 Figure 1A; 
 Smith, 1968; 
 Burle et al., 2004).
